description: From Latin vāticinātus, perfect passive participle of vāticinor (“foretell, prophesy”).

verbs.description: vaticinate (third-person singular simple present vaticinates, present participle vaticinating, simple past and past participle vaticinated)

entries.meaning: (transitive, intransitive, chiefly formal) To predict or foretell future events; to prophesy or presage.
